      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=roguetactic&amp;message.id=855#M855</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;This may be a bit long winded but I'll try my best to keep it simple.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;Overview:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Two characters involved&lt;/strong&gt; - Myself , lvl 70 shaman and my rogue, lvl 53.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The problem&lt;/strong&gt; - Renux is TLC'ing the Jagged Diamond Dagger&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;A more in-depth explanation:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fight 1&lt;/strong&gt; - I find Yendar, do the turn in, and notice Renux con's light blue to Shaman. I say to myself &amp;quot;Sweet, I can group the rogue and shaman for this fight because light blues do not TLC&amp;quot;.  Apperantly I was wrong. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So I petition to be given the Jagged Diamond Dagger, in hind sight I should of realized Sony could not give that to me because they have no record of it. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I went into Trader Mode for the night and when I woke up I had a response saying &amp;quot;We cannot give you the dagger, but here is the &amp;quot;Scribbled Parchment&amp;quot; back so you can turn that into Yendar.&amp;quot;  I re-petition and explain  &amp;quot;okay, thats fine, but if thats the route we're taking, can I have my Book of Souls back too?&amp;quot; (The petition was more detailed then that,but thats the jist of it).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I leave for work, staying in Trader Mode, and tripled checked my inventory to make sure I had room for them to put the Book of Souls there.   I return home from work with a GM response of &amp;quot;Our records show that you dropped the Book of Souls and someone else picked it up, we can't help you&amp;quot;.  Now *that* made me mad.  It was the GM's fault it dropped, not mine. But I figured at this point, its a trust issue. They don't know that I really didnt drop it.  So I sucked it up, considered myself lucky that I at least got the Scribbled Parchment and went back to Hate and got my book again.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fight 2 - &lt;/strong&gt;Now I return to Steamfont. I decide this time, I'm going to keep the Shaman outside the group and just have her slow and heal and maybe add some Puppy Damage. I spawn Renux, have Puppy attack for a BRIEF amount of time before pulling him off and then slow and heal to keep aggro while my Rogue does damage from the back.  I kill Renux and ~gasp~ this fight was TRIVIAL to me. My Jagged Diamond Dagger has poofed once again.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; Now I look back and forth between my Rogue and Shaman screen. The Shaman did not KS the fight or she would of gotten the TLC message. Only the Rogue got the message. I *know* I did more damage then the Shaman.  So, frustrated, I petition to get my Tattered Parchement and Book of Souls back, then go to bed. I wake up to a GM saying &amp;quot;We can't give you the Tattered Parchment and Book of Souls from Renux because you didnt loot them off her.&amp;quot;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; ((This is where my jaw hit the keyboard)).  If the GM had read the petition they would know that is *not* what I was saying.   So I  petitioned and gave a very good description of my situation. I'm at work now, so we'll see what the response is when I get home.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;My Question: &lt;/strong&gt;What am I doing wrong? The first TLC I'm going to chaulk up to having the 70 grouped when I killed Renux. The second fight I am very confused about. My Rogue did the most damage, Renux should not of TLC'd. I've been playing on FV since it was in Beta, I am aware of how the system works and from everything I've seen, this should not of happened. Is it that Puppy did damage, no matter how minimal? Would 1 point of damage make this fight TLC for the Rogue?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Possible Solution: &lt;/strong&gt;Those that play on FV know that going into /raid mode can negate TLC, but I personally have witnessed something TLC even though I was in raid mode, so I am wary of trying. I want to be 100% sure before I try this fight again.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I am frustrated with the petition system, the GM's never seem to really understand what I'm saying and I'm worried that they wont reimburse me the items again because I've asked for them back twice now. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Has anyone else on FV dealt with this?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Thank you for any help.&lt;/div&gt;</description>
